The REEVES MANUFACTURING COMPANY v. The LOME COMPANY and The Stay-On Manufacturing Company. No. 7852. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 15, 1937. Frease & Bishop, of Canton, Ohio, for appellant. Fay, Oberlin & Fay, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellees.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the motion df appellant to docket and dismiss appeal be, and it is, granted.

Appeal docketed and dismissed.
